For each seed packet, include as many of the following as you can (I’ll map them to the right MARC fields):

Information Type	Example	MARC Field
Common name	Purple Coneflower	245 ‡a
Scientific name	Echinacea purpurea	245 ‡b
Variety or cultivar	Magnus	250 or 500
Collector or donor	Mid-Atlantic Regional Seed Bank	100/110
Collection number or ID	MARSB-2025-031	099 or 024
Year collected	2024	260/264 ‡c
Source (wild, garden, etc.)	Garden grown from native source	500 note
Germination or viability rate	85% germination	500 note
Storage location or accession number	Freezer 2, shelf 4	852 or 090
Quantity (seeds)	200 seeds	300 or 500
Region or provenance	Prince George’s County, MD	651 or 500
Keywords (habitat, uses, etc.)	Pollinator plant, native prairie	650
Image or barcode (if any)	file name or link	856 or 024



Example Output (MARC-style record)

